{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"As a culture, we tell ourselves lots of stories"},{"time":3000,"text":"about the future,"},{"time":5000,"text":"and where we might move forward from this point."},{"time":7000,"text":"Some of those stories are that"},{"time":9000,"text":"somebody is just going to sort everything out for us."},{"time":12000,"text":"Other stories are that everything is on the verge of unraveling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16000,"text":"But I want to tell you a different story here today."},{"time":18000,"text":"Like all stories, it has a beginning."},{"time":21000,"text":"My work, for a long time, has been involved in education,"},{"time":24000,"text":"in teaching people practical skills"},{"time":26000,"text":"for sustainability,"},{"time":28000,"text":"teaching people how to take responsibility"},{"time":30000,"text":"for growing some of their own food,"},{"time":32000,"text":"how to build buildings using local materials,"},{"time":34000,"text":"how to generate their own energy, and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"I lived in Ireland, built the first straw-bale houses in Ireland,"},{"time":41000,"text":"and some cob buildings and all this kind of thing."},{"time":44000,"text":"But all my work for many years was focused"},{"time":47000,"text":"around the idea that sustainability"},{"time":49000,"text":"means basically looking at"},{"time":51000,"text":"the globalized economic growth model,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and moderating what comes in at one end,"},{"time":56000,"text":"and moderating the outputs at the other end."},{"time":59000,"text":"And then I came into contact with a way of looking at things"},{"time":62000,"text":"which actually changed that profoundly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"And in order to introduce you to that,"},{"time":66000,"text":"I've got something here that I'm going to unveil,"},{"time":68000,"text":"which is one of the great marvels of the modern age."},{"time":71000,"text":"And it's something so astounding and so astonishing"},{"time":73000,"text":"that I think maybe as I remove this cloth"},{"time":76000,"text":"a suitable gasp of amazement might be appropriate."},{"time":79000,"text":"If you could help me with that it would be fantastic."},{"time":86000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":87000,"text":"This is a liter of oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"This bottle of oil,"},{"time":93000,"text":"distilled over a hundred million years of geological time,"},{"time":96000,"text":"ancient sunlight,"},{"time":98000,"text":"contains the energy equivalent of about five weeks"},{"time":100000,"text":"hard human manual labor --"},{"time":103000,"text":"equivalent to about 35 strong people"},{"time":107000,"text":"coming round and working for you."},{"time":110000,"text":"We can turn it into a dazzling array of materials,"},{"time":114000,"text":"medicine, modern clothing,"},{"time":116000,"text":"laptops, a whole range of different things."},{"time":120000,"text":"It gives us an energy return that's unimaginable, historically."},{"time":125000,"text":"We've based the design of our settlements,"},{"time":127000,"text":"our business models, our transport plans,"},{"time":129000,"text":"even the idea of economic growth, some would argue,"},{"time":132000,"text":"on the assumption that we will have this in perpetuity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"Yet, when we take a step back,"},{"time":139000,"text":"and look over the span of history,"},{"time":141000,"text":"at what we might call the petroleum interval,"},{"time":144000,"text":"it's a short period in history"},{"time":146000,"text":"where we've discovered this extraordinary material,"},{"time":149000,"text":"and then based a whole way of life around it."},{"time":152000,"text":"But as we straddle the top of this energy mountain, at this stage,"},{"time":156000,"text":"we move from a time where our economic success,"},{"time":159000,"text":"our sense of individual prowess and well-being"},{"time":162000,"text":"is directly linked to how much of this we consume,"},{"time":166000,"text":"to a time when actually our degree of oil dependency"},{"time":169000,"text":"is our degree of vulnerability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"And it's increasingly clear that we"},{"time":173000,"text":"aren't going to be able to rely on the fact that"},{"time":175000,"text":"we're going to have this at our disposal forever."},{"time":178000,"text":"For every four barrels of oil that we consume,"},{"time":180000,"text":"we only discover one."},{"time":182000,"text":"And that gap continues to widen."},{"time":184000,"text":"There is also the fact that the amount of energy"},{"time":186000,"text":"that we get back from the oil that we discover is falling."},{"time":189000,"text":"In the 1930s we got 100 units of energy back"},{"time":192000,"text":"for every one that we put in to extract it."},{"time":195000,"text":"Completely unprecedented, historically."},{"time":197000,"text":"Already that's fallen to about 11."},{"time":199000,"text":"And that's why, now,"},{"time":201000,"text":"the new breakthroughs, the new frontiers"},{"time":203000,"text":"in terms of oil extraction are scrambling about in Alberta,"},{"time":206000,"text":"or at the bottom of the oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"There are 98 oil-producing nations in the world."},{"time":211000,"text":"But of those, 65 have already passed their peak."},{"time":214000,"text":"The moment when the world on average passes this peak,"},{"time":217000,"text":"people wonder when that's going to happen."},{"time":219000,"text":"And there is an emerging case"},{"time":220000,"text":"that maybe that was what happened last July"},{"time":222000,"text":"when the oil prices were so high."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"But are we to assume that the same brilliance"},{"time":226000,"text":"and creativity and adaptability"},{"time":228000,"text":"that got us up to the top of that energy mountain in the first place"},{"time":231000,"text":"is somehow mysteriously going to evaporate"},{"time":234000,"text":"when we have to design a creative way back down the other side?"},{"time":238000,"text":"No. But the thinking that we have to come up with"},{"time":241000,"text":"has to be based on a realistic assessment"},{"time":244000,"text":"of where we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246000,"text":"There is also the issue of climate change,"},{"time":248000,"text":"is the other thing that underpins this transition approach."},{"time":250000,"text":"But the thing that I notice, as I talk to climate scientists,"},{"time":253000,"text":"is the increasingly terrified look they have in their eyes,"},{"time":256000,"text":"as the data that's coming in,"},{"time":258000,"text":"which is far ahead of what the IPCC are talking about."},{"time":262000,"text":"So the IPCC said"},{"time":264000,"text":"that we might see significant breakup"},{"time":266000,"text":"of the arctic ice in 2100, in their worst case scenario."},{"time":269000,"text":"Actually, if current trends continue,"},{"time":272000,"text":"it could all be gone in five or 10 years' time."},{"time":274000,"text":"If just three percent of the carbon locked up in the arctic permafrost"},{"time":278000,"text":"is released as the world warms,"},{"time":280000,"text":"it would offset all the savings that we need to make,"},{"time":282000,"text":"in carbon, over the next 40 years to avoid runaway climate change."},{"time":285000,"text":"We have no choice other than deep and urgent decarbonization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"But I'm always very interested to think about"},{"time":292000,"text":"what might the stories be"},{"time":294000,"text":"that the generations further down the slope from us"},{"time":297000,"text":"are going to tell about us."},{"time":299000,"text":"\"The generation that lived at the top of the mountain,"},{"time":302000,"text":"that partied so hard, and so abused its inheritance.\""},{"time":307000,"text":"And one of the ways I like to do that"},{"time":309000,"text":"is to look back at the stories people used to tell"},{"time":311000,"text":"before we had cheap oil, before we had fossil fuels,"},{"time":314000,"text":"and people relied on their own muscle, animal muscle energy,"},{"time":317000,"text":"or a little bit of wind, little bit of water energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"We had stories like \"The Seven-League Boots\":"},{"time":323000,"text":"the giant who had these boots, where, once you put them on,"},{"time":325000,"text":"with every stride you could cover seven leagues, or 21 miles,"},{"time":329000,"text":"a kind of travel completely unimaginable"},{"time":331000,"text":"to people without that kind of energy at their disposal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334000,"text":"Stories like The Magic Porridge Pot,"},{"time":337000,"text":"where you had a pot where if you knew the magic words,"},{"time":339000,"text":"this pot would just make as much food as you liked,"},{"time":342000,"text":"without you having to do any work,"},{"time":344000,"text":"provided you could remember the other magic word to stop it making porridge."},{"time":347000,"text":"Otherwise you'd flood your entire town with warm porridge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"There is the story of \"The Elves and the Shoemaker.\""},{"time":354000,"text":"The people who make shoes go to sleep, wake up in the morning,"},{"time":356000,"text":"and all the shoes are magically made for them."},{"time":358000,"text":"It's something that was unimaginable to people then."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"Now we have the seven-league boots"},{"time":364000,"text":"in the form of Ryanair and Easyjet."},{"time":367000,"text":"We have the magic porridge pot"},{"time":369000,"text":"in the form of Walmart and Tesco."},{"time":371000,"text":"And we have the elves in the form of China."},{"time":374000,"text":"But we don't appreciate what an astonishing"},{"time":378000,"text":"thing that has been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"And what are the stories that we tell ourselves now,"},{"time":382000,"text":"as we look forward about where we're going to go."},{"time":385000,"text":"And I would argue that there are four. There is the idea of business as usual,"},{"time":388000,"text":"that the future will be like the present, just more of it."},{"time":391000,"text":"But as we've seen over the last year, I think that's an idea"},{"time":393000,"text":"that is increasingly coming into question."},{"time":395000,"text":"And in terms of climate change,"},{"time":397000,"text":"is something that is not actually feasible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"There is the idea of hitting the wall,"},{"time":403000,"text":"that actually somehow everything is so fragile"},{"time":406000,"text":"that it might just all unravel and collapse."},{"time":408000,"text":"This is a popular story in some places."},{"time":411000,"text":"The third story is the idea that technology can solve everything,"},{"time":414000,"text":"that technology can somehow get us through this completely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"And it's an idea that I think is very prevalent at these TED Talks,"},{"time":422000,"text":"the idea that we can invent our way out of a profound"},{"time":425000,"text":"economic and energy crisis,"},{"time":427000,"text":"that a move to a knowledge economy"},{"time":429000,"text":"can somehow neatly sidestep those energy constraints,"},{"time":432000,"text":"the idea that we'll discover some fabulous new source of energy"},{"time":435000,"text":"that will mean we can sweep all concerns"},{"time":437000,"text":"about energy security to one side,"},{"time":440000,"text":"the idea that we can step off neatly"},{"time":442000,"text":"onto a completely renewable world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"But the world isn't Second Life."},{"time":446000,"text":"We can't create new land and new energy systems at the click of a mouse."},{"time":450000,"text":"And as we sit, exchanging free ideas with each other,"},{"time":453000,"text":"there are still people mining coal"},{"time":455000,"text":"in order to power the servers, extracting the minerals"},{"time":457000,"text":"to make all of those things."},{"time":459000,"text":"The breakfast that we eat as we sit down"},{"time":461000,"text":"to check our email in the morning"},{"time":463000,"text":"is still transported at great distances,"},{"time":465000,"text":"usually at the expense of the local, more resilient"},{"time":467000,"text":"food systems that would have supplied that in the past,"},{"time":470000,"text":"which we've so effectively devalued and dismantled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474000,"text":"We can be astonishingly inventive and creative."},{"time":477000,"text":"But we also live in a world with very real constraints and demands."},{"time":481000,"text":"Energy and technology are not the same thing."},{"time":484000,"text":"What I'm involved with is the transition response."},{"time":486000,"text":"And this is really about looking the challenges"},{"time":489000,"text":"of peak oil and climate change square in the face,"},{"time":491000,"text":"and responding with a creativity and an adaptability"},{"time":494000,"text":"and an imagination that we really need."},{"time":497000,"text":"It's something which has spread incredibly fast."},{"time":500000,"text":"And it is something which has several characteristics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502000,"text":"It's viral. It seems to spread under the radar very, very quickly."},{"time":507000,"text":"It's open source. It's something which everybody who's involved with it"},{"time":511000,"text":"develops and passes on as they work with it."},{"time":515000,"text":"It's self-organizing. There is no great central organization"},{"time":518000,"text":"that pushes this; people just pick up an idea"},{"time":520000,"text":"and they run with it, and they implement it where they are."},{"time":523000,"text":"It's solutions-focused. It's very much looking at what people can do"},{"time":526000,"text":"where they are, to respond to this."},{"time":529000,"text":"It's sensitive to place and to scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"Transitional is completely different."},{"time":533000,"text":"Transition groups in Chile, transition groups in the U.S., transition groups here,"},{"time":537000,"text":"what they're doing looks very different in every place that you go to."},{"time":540000,"text":"It learns very much from its mistakes."},{"time":542000,"text":"And it feels historic. It tries to create a sense"},{"time":545000,"text":"that this is a historic opportunity"},{"time":547000,"text":"to do something really extraordinary."},{"time":549000,"text":"And it's a process which is really joyful."},{"time":551000,"text":"People have a huge amount of fun doing this,"},{"time":553000,"text":"reconnecting with other people as they do it."},{"time":556000,"text":"One of the things that underpins it is this idea of resilience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"And I think, in many ways, the idea of resilience"},{"time":562000,"text":"is a more useful concept than the idea of sustainability."},{"time":566000,"text":"The idea of resilience comes from the study of ecology."},{"time":568000,"text":"And it's really about how systems,"},{"time":571000,"text":"settlements, withstand shock from the outside."},{"time":574000,"text":"When they encounter shock from the outside"},{"time":576000,"text":"that they don't just unravel and fall to pieces."},{"time":578000,"text":"And I think it's a more useful concept than sustainability, as I said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"When our supermarkets have only two or three days' worth of food in them"},{"time":586000,"text":"at any one time, often sustainability tends to focus on"},{"time":589000,"text":"the energy efficiency of the freezers"},{"time":591000,"text":"and on the packaging that the lettuces are wrapped up in."},{"time":594000,"text":"Looking through the lens of resilience,"},{"time":596000,"text":"we really question how we've let ourselves get into a situation"},{"time":600000,"text":"that's so vulnerable."},{"time":602000,"text":"Resilience runs much deeper:"},{"time":604000,"text":"it's about building modularity into what we do,"},{"time":606000,"text":"building surge breakers into how we organize the basic things that support us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"This is a photograph of the Bristol and District"},{"time":613000,"text":"Market Gardeners Association, in 1897."},{"time":617000,"text":"This is at a time when the city of Bristol,"},{"time":619000,"text":"which is quite close to here,"},{"time":621000,"text":"was surrounded by commercial market gardens,"},{"time":623000,"text":"which provided a significant amount of the food"},{"time":626000,"text":"that was consumed in the town, and created a lot of employment for people, as well."},{"time":630000,"text":"There was a degree of resilience, if you like, at that time,"},{"time":633000,"text":"which we can now only look back on with envy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637000,"text":"So how does this transition idea work?"},{"time":639000,"text":"So basically, you have a group of people who are excited by the idea."},{"time":642000,"text":"They pick up some of the tools that we've developed."},{"time":645000,"text":"They start to run an awareness-raising program"},{"time":647000,"text":"looking at how this might actually work in the town."},{"time":650000,"text":"They show films, they give talks, and so on."},{"time":652000,"text":"It's a process which is playful and creative"},{"time":655000,"text":"and informative."},{"time":657000,"text":"Then they start to form working groups, looking at different aspects of this,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and then from that, there emerge a whole lot of projects"},{"time":663000,"text":"which then the transition project itself"},{"time":665000,"text":"starts to support and enable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"So it started out with some work I was involved in in Ireland,"},{"time":672000,"text":"where I was teaching, and has since spread."},{"time":674000,"text":"There are now over 200 formal transition projects."},{"time":677000,"text":"And there are thousands of others who are at what we call the mulling stage."},{"time":681000,"text":"They are mulling whether they're going to take it further."},{"time":683000,"text":"And actually a lot of them are doing huge amounts of stuff."},{"time":686000,"text":"But what do they actually do? You know, it's a kind of nice idea,"},{"time":688000,"text":"but what do they actually do on the ground?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":690000,"text":"Well, I think it's really important to make the point that actually"},{"time":694000,"text":"you know, this isn't something which is going to do everything on its own."},{"time":697000,"text":"We need international legislation from Copenhagen and so on."},{"time":701000,"text":"We need national responses. We need local government responses."},{"time":704000,"text":"But all of those things are going to be much easier"},{"time":707000,"text":"if we have communities that are vibrant and coming up with ideas"},{"time":710000,"text":"and leading from the front, making unelectable policies electable,"},{"time":713000,"text":"over the next 5 to 10 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715000,"text":"Some of the things that emerge from it are local food projects,"},{"time":718000,"text":"like community-supported agriculture schemes,"},{"time":720000,"text":"urban food production, creating local food directories, and so on."},{"time":724000,"text":"A lot of places now are starting to set up their own energy companies,"},{"time":727000,"text":"community-owned energy companies,"},{"time":729000,"text":"where the community can invest money into itself,"},{"time":731000,"text":"to start putting in place"},{"time":733000,"text":"the kind of renewable energy infrastructure that we need."},{"time":735000,"text":"A lot of places are working with their local schools."},{"time":738000,"text":"Newent in the Forest of Dean: big polytunnel they built for the school;"},{"time":740000,"text":"the kids are learning how to grow food."},{"time":742000,"text":"Promoting recycling, things like garden-share,"},{"time":745000,"text":"that matches up people who don't have a garden"},{"time":747000,"text":"who would like to grow food, with people who have gardens they aren't using anymore."},{"time":750000,"text":"Planting productive trees throughout urban spaces."},{"time":753000,"text":"And also starting to play around with the idea of"},{"time":755000,"text":"alternative currencies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"This is Lewes in Sussex,"},{"time":759000,"text":"who have recently launched the Lewes Pound,"},{"time":762000,"text":"a currency that you can only spend within the town,"},{"time":764000,"text":"as a way of starting to cycle money within the local economy."},{"time":767000,"text":"You take it anywhere else, it's not worth anything."},{"time":769000,"text":"But actually within the town you start to create these economic"},{"time":772000,"text":"cycles much more effectively."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Another thing that they do is what we call an energy descent plan,"},{"time":777000,"text":"which is basically to develop a plan B for the town."},{"time":780000,"text":"Most of our local authorities, when they sit down to plan"},{"time":783000,"text":"for the next five, 10, 15, 20 years of a community,"},{"time":786000,"text":"still start by assuming that there will be more energy,"},{"time":789000,"text":"more cars, more housing,"},{"time":791000,"text":"more jobs, more growth, and so on."},{"time":793000,"text":"What does it look like if that's not the case? And how can we embrace that"},{"time":796000,"text":"and actually come up with something that was actually more likely"},{"time":798000,"text":"to sustain everybody?"},{"time":800000,"text":"As a friend of mine says, \"Life is a series of things you're not quite ready for.\""},{"time":805000,"text":"And that's certainly been my experience with transition."},{"time":807000,"text":"From three years ago, it just being an idea,"},{"time":809000,"text":"this has become something that has virally swept around the world."},{"time":813000,"text":"We're getting a lot of interest from government. Ed Miliband,"},{"time":815000,"text":"the energy minister of this country, was invited to come to our recent conference"},{"time":819000,"text":"as a keynote listener."},{"time":821000,"text":"Which he did --"},{"time":823000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":824000,"text":"(Applause) --"},{"time":827000,"text":"and has since become a great advocate of the whole idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":831000,"text":"There are now two local authorities in this country"},{"time":834000,"text":"who have declared themselves transitional local authorities,"},{"time":836000,"text":"Leicestershire and Somerset. And in Stroud,"},{"time":838000,"text":"the transition group there, in effect, wrote the local government's food plan."},{"time":843000,"text":"And the head of the council said,"},{"time":845000,"text":"\"If we didn't have Transition Stroud, we would have to invent"},{"time":847000,"text":"all of that community infrastructure for the first time.\""},{"time":851000,"text":"As we see the spread of it, we see national hubs emerging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":854000,"text":"In Scotland, the Scottish government's climate change fund"},{"time":857000,"text":"has funded Transition Scotland"},{"time":859000,"text":"as a national organization supporting the spread of this."},{"time":862000,"text":"And we see it all over the place as well now."},{"time":865000,"text":"But the key to transition is thinking not that we have to change everything now,"},{"time":868000,"text":"but that things are already inevitably changing,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and what we need to do is to work creatively with that,"},{"time":874000,"text":"based on asking the right questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"I think I'd like to just return at the end"},{"time":879000,"text":"to the idea of stories."},{"time":881000,"text":"Because I think stories are vital here."},{"time":883000,"text":"And actually the stories that we tell ourselves,"},{"time":885000,"text":"we have a huge dearth of stories about how to move forward creatively from here."},{"time":890000,"text":"And one of the key things that transition does"},{"time":892000,"text":"is to pull those stories out of what people are doing."},{"time":894000,"text":"Stories about the community that's produced"},{"time":897000,"text":"its own 21 pound note, for example,"},{"time":900000,"text":"the school that's turned its car park into a food garden,"},{"time":903000,"text":"the community that's founded its own energy company."},{"time":906000,"text":"And for me, one of the great stories recently"},{"time":908000,"text":"was the Obamas digging up the south lawn of the White House"},{"time":911000,"text":"to create a vegetable garden. Because the last time that was done,"},{"time":913000,"text":"when Eleanor Roosevelt did it,"},{"time":915000,"text":"it led to the creation of 20 million vegetable gardens across the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920000,"text":"So the question I'd like to leave you with, really,"},{"time":922000,"text":"is -- for all aspects of the things that your community needs"},{"time":926000,"text":"in order to thrive,"},{"time":928000,"text":"how can it be done in such a way"},{"time":930000,"text":"that drastically reduces its carbon emissions,"},{"time":933000,"text":"while also building resilience?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":935000,"text":"Personally, I feel enormously grateful"},{"time":937000,"text":"to have lived through the age of cheap oil."},{"time":940000,"text":"I've been astonishingly lucky, we've been astonishingly lucky."},{"time":944000,"text":"But let us honor what it has bought us,"},{"time":946000,"text":"and move forward from this point."},{"time":948000,"text":"Because if we cling to it, and continue to assume"},{"time":950000,"text":"that it can underpin our choices,"},{"time":953000,"text":"the future that it presents to us is one which is really unmanageable."},{"time":956000,"text":"And by loving and leaving all that oil has done for us,"},{"time":959000,"text":"and that the Oil Age has done for us,"},{"time":961000,"text":"we are able to then begin the creation"},{"time":963000,"text":"of a world which is more resilient,"},{"time":966000,"text":"more nourishing,"},{"time":968000,"text":"and in which, we find ourselves fitter, more skilled"},{"time":971000,"text":"and more connected to each other."},{"time":973000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":975000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}